You are working **inside** the `asciisd/nova-chat` Laravel Nova package.
Before any non-trivial edit, consult the per-area guidelines and skills
in `.ai/`.

## Always-on guidelines (load these eagerly)

- `.ai/guidelines/package-architecture.md` — repo layout + request flow.
- `.ai/guidelines/contract-purity.md` — the rule of this repo: no
  app-namespaced classes inside `src/`.
- `.ai/guidelines/frontend-workflow.md` — Vue conventions, committed
  `dist/`, polling design.
- `.ai/guidelines/api-design.md` — the five-route public API surface.
- `.ai/guidelines/database-schema.md` — required columns + why
  `is_from_admin` is denormalized.

## On-demand skills (load when the task matches)

| User intent | Read |
|---|---|
| Add a new feature to the package | `.ai/skills/add-package-feature/SKILL.md` |
| Edit anything in `resources/js/` | `.ai/skills/update-vue-ui/SKILL.md` |
| Cut a tagged release | `.ai/skills/release-new-version/SKILL.md` |
| Sync `resources/boost/` after a code change | `.ai/skills/sync-boost-resources/SKILL.md` |

## Two audiences — do not confuse them

- `.ai/` is for **maintainers of this repo**.
- `resources/boost/` is for **consumers** of the package via Laravel
  Boost. Don't conflate them.

## Hard rules (every PR)

- Never reference `App\Models\…` from `src/`, `routes/`, `config/`, or
  `database/stubs/`.
- Never edit `dist/js/tool.js` or `dist/js/tool.css` by hand — they are
  generated by `npm run build` and committed verbatim.
- Never recompute `is_from_admin` at query time.
- Never change the wire format under `/nova-vendor/nova-chat/*` without
  bumping major.
- Whenever consumer-visible behavior changes, also update
  `resources/boost/guidelines/nova-chat.md`,
  `resources/boost/skills/nova-chat-development/SKILL.md`,
  `database/stubs/chat_messages_table.stub`, and the README — in the
  same PR.
